		<td><b>Re: What is your favorite video game console?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It has to be a toss-up between NES and SNES.  NES debuted many of the pioneering series of console gaming (Mario, Zelda, Metroid, Final Fantasy, Dragon Quest, Castlevania, Megaman and so on...) while their SNES sequels added lots of polish to the basic idea.  SNES would get a slight nod because games are no longer extremely difficult due to limited game engines (Compare Zelda I, Castlevania I-III with LTTP and Castlevania IV).  Plus I find it to be the first console where graphic design could be enchanting with Chrono Trigger, Yoshi's Island and such.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


