		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd have to say it depends on mood. Personal Computer wins by a mile if we allow it, though, simply because editing utilities for games are far-more-often available and/or included, along with more generally programming things for it being easy rather than intentionally sealed away.<br /><br />is the TI-99/4A on there yet?<br /><br />A toss-up between N64, SNES, and Dreamcast, though, for multiplayer memories.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">no longer so hard because of limited game engines</div>Less a function of the console; I'd argue, than developer/industry experience level...comparing Link's Awakening and Zelda 1 seems more apt.

		

